#title
Bankrate Content Feeds

#description
Bankrate content feeds are a content syndication service that allows partner websites to publish Bankrate's trusted financial content. Through feeds, partners receive a continuous stream of articles, guides, and resources covering personal finance topics.

::

::page-section
## Integration Types

Bankrate offers two integration models. The right choice depends on how your platform renders content and what your tracking requirements are.

| | Attribution-Enriched | Attribution-Only |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **Hosted by** | MyFinance | Bankrate |
| **Content rendering** | MyFinance embeds widgets and tracking in article bodies | Partner renders content; links back to Bankrate |
| **Tracking** | Automatic — zero config required | Attribution query parameters on article URLs (set via the feed) |
| **Best for** | Full content syndication with embedded financial tools | Simple link-back integrations |

---

## How It Works

1. **Content Creation:** Bankrate's editorial team creates high-quality financial content
2. **Feed Generation:** Content is automatically formatted and delivered through feeds
3. **Partner Integration:** Partners consume feeds and display content on their websites
4. **Attribution:** Content is properly attributed to Bankrate with tracking

