## Technical Guide

## Option A: Attribution-Enriched Feeds (via MyFinance)

This is the full-featured integration. Article bodies are delivered with embedded financial widgets and tracking handled automatically by MyFinance. No additional code is required to capture clicks or downstream revenue.

### Base URL

```text
https://www.myfinance.com/rss/syndication/
```

### Endpoint

```text
GET {base_url}/{feed_name}/{content_source_identifier}
```

### Query Parameters

| Parameter | Required | Value | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| `type` | No | `"xml"` | Sets `Content-Type` to `text/xml; charset=UTF-8` |
| `page` | No | integer | Pagination |
| `from_date` | No | YYYY-MM-DD | Pull content from a specific date; useful for backfilling |
| `to_date` | No | YYYY-MM-DD | Upper bound for `from_date` filtering |

`Content-Type` defaults to `application/rss+xml; charset=utf-8` when `type` is not set.

### Per Page

Feeds default to 20 articles per page. This is controlled by the feed delivery system and cannot be modified on the request.

### RSS Response Example

