## Option B: Attribution-Only Feeds (via Bankrate)

This integration is designed for partners who want to link back to Bankrate articles directly — without embedding full content or relying on MyFinance. Article URLs in the feed are automatically decorated with attribution query parameters that tie traffic back to your account.

No widgets are embedded. Your platform is responsible for rendering titles, excerpts, images, and linking users through to Bankrate.

### Feed URL Structure

```text
GET https://www.bankrate.com/feeds/{feed_slug}/{format}/{per_page}/{page}
```

| Segment | Required | Description |
| --- | --- | --- |
| `feed_slug` | Yes | Unique identifier for your feed, provided by Bankrate |
| `format` | No | Response format (see [Formats](#formats) below) |
| `per_page` | No | Number of articles per page (integer, max 100) |
| `page` | No | Page number (integer) |

### Feed Query Parameters

| Parameter | Required | Value | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| `from_date` | No | YYYY-MM-DD | Return content published on or after this date |

### Attribution Query Parameters

Each article URL in the feed response will include attribution query parameters configured for your account (e.g. `?pid=your-partner-id`). These are appended automatically — no changes are needed on your side.

### Formats

The `format` segment controls the response structure. If omitted, `rss` is used by default.

| Format | Description |
| --- | --- |
| `rss` | Standard RSS 2.0 (default) |
| `xml` | XML format |
| `json` | JSON |
| `jsonreduced` | Reduced-field JSON |
| `extended` | Extended XML with additional metadata fields |
| `extended-content` | Extended XML including full article body |

